main event: An object was observed in Point Arena, California for 89 minutes on 4 November 1956.
interesting points: The object was slightly larger than a star and moved slowly in a southerly direction., The sighting lasted for 89 minutes., The report suggested multiple possible identifications for the object including a balloon, satellite, aircraft, or meteor., Observations indicated that winds and duration likely suggested the object was caused by a satellite or orbiting vehicle., No photographs were included in the report.
sighted object: an unidentified object moving in the sky
